12/08/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Police arrested six people Tuesday (August 11th) suspected of drug trafficking.
Authorities seized 143kg of marijuana and 2.5kg of hashish in two separate operations.
The cannabis was found in a truck parked at the port of Corfu.
Two Greek nationals and three foreigners -- an Albanian, a Belgian and a Romanian -- were arrested.
The hashish was found in Patra, on a foreign national who was also detained.
(Kathimerini - 12/08/09;
MIA - 11/08/09)
